  "decision_notes": "The problem requires deriving the force law for a polymer chain under adiabatic (thermally isolated) conditions, which differs from the standard isothermal case due to the temperature dependence on extension.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "statistical_mechanics_expert",
      "instructions": "Derive the partition function and the Helmholtz free energy F(x, T) for a freely jointed chain of n segments of length l at extension x and temperature T. Provide the expression for the entropy S(x, T) and the internal energy U(x, T) as functions of x, T, and n."
    },
    {
      "label": "thermodynamics_expert",
      "instructions": "Given the internal energy U(x, T) and entropy S(x, T) of a freely jointed chain, apply the adiabatic condition (dS = 0) to find the relationship between temperature T and extension x. Then, use the first law of thermodynamics for an adiabatic process to derive the force F(x) = (dU/dx)_S."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the entropy and internal energy expressions to find the adiabatic constraint T(x). Substitute this T(x) into the expression for the internal energy to find U(x) under adiabatic conditions, then differentiate U(x) with respect to x to obtain the final force law F(x)."
}

